item.title: About
item.dc:creator: wtccnwatkins
item.content:encoded:
About we

Vicious Cycles was founded out of a sort of cringe-worthyness. That cringe-wrothiness we're referring to is the sight of so many Triangle bikers having to put up with low-quality, expensive bikes. That's like cornbread at the price of a 200-year-old wine. No, just...no. That's not cool. We, on the other hand, can offer you something better, something you bikers are starving for. So come see us and we can show the other shops in the Triangle a thing or about about quality bikes.

item.title: Another dope, fresh-off-the-shelves model from Mairose
item.dc:creator: wtccnwatkins
item.content:encoded: Yes, you read that right! Get ready mountain lovers, because it's the all new Mairose 26 Inch Mountain Bike Carbon Steel 21 Speed Bicycle! It's an MTB Bike complete with a K-Type Shock-Absorbing Double Disc Brake! The mountains are sure to fear even the sight of this baby! And guess what? It's all for the low price of $135! That's a pretty cheap price for a chance to crush the mountains! But wait! That's not all! Order between 9-10 AM on the third Saturday of each month and you can get 20% off on this rad model!

item.title: It's all about the kids for this one!
item.dc:creator: wtccnwatkins
item.content:encoded: We cover a lot of bikes for adults, but what about those that aren't quite there yet? Well, kiddos, we got something totally rad for ya! You'll totally dig the newest model of the Brave Sterling Blue Freestyle BMX Kids 20" Bicycle! It's got Lightweight Aluminum Frame and Fork, is really easy to ride on, includes high-class parts/safety, and all without the high-class price! That's right, this baby only costs $250! This is like Dijon ketchup at a Heinz price! Kiddos will be rocking the BMX course with this one!

item.title: Here's another great one for you e-bike fans!
item.dc:creator: wtccnwatkins
item.content:encoded: We've got a great one for you guys that like to charge your bikes! It's the brand new Aostirmotor Electric Mounain Bike, complete with a 750W Motor, 26 4.0 Fat Tire Bicycle, and 48V 10.4AH Removable Lithium Electric Battery! And all of it for a low price tag, too: $1,150! With this puppy, you'll be electrifying both the road and the mountains as well! Get ready, road and mountains! You're about to get shocked! Oh and by the way, you can get 25% of this baby if you order at any time of the day where are consecutive numbers (ex. 1:11, 2:22, 3:33, ect.)!

item.title: About I
item.dc:creator: wtccnwatkins
item.content:encoded: My name is Nate Watkins and I'm 26 years old. Although I was born in Durham, North Carolina, I lived for about 10 years in Germany before moving back to the state I was born in. The major I chose for myself is graphic design, which I already have a certificate in, so I at least know that I have a future in this field. I also hope to get a job at a graphic design shop or another type of company making awesome designs someday. Although I don't have any professional experience in graphic design (yet), I've been going to Wake Tech Community College in Raleigh, North Carolina, for an accumulative total of 3 years to study it, and my hard work has resulted in my getting certified last year. I've been training using various Adobe apps, namely Photoshop, InDesign, and Illustrator. I am autistic, so I have a very keen sense of detail and if I try hard enough, I can let my creative mind really do it's work and create wonderful and beautiful designs. I believe that, in terms of progress, graphic design has come a long way in recent decades, especially in the 21st century. I could only imagine how much more complicated graphic design was decades ago than it is today, and I can only imagine how much progress the field of graphic designing will make in the coming years/decades. I hope whatever changes may happen to graphic design will be for the better. The profession of graphic design does not deserve to regress back to where it was decades ago, before graphic design could be done electronically.
